\ Revised `to`: at the REPL it auto-creates a global on first assignment;
\ inside a definition an undeclared target is a clear error.

\ auto-create on first assignment, then read
4 to x
x . cr

\ reassignment of the auto-created global
9 to x
x . cr

\ holds any value, not just floats
[ 1 2 3 ] to arr
arr . cr

\ explicit `variable` still works alongside auto-create
variable v
5 to v
v . cr

\ inside a definition, an undeclared target errors (can't allocate mid-compile)
: bad 1 to undeclared ;
